</td>
<td style="text-align: left;" valign="top">
<h1><span style="font-size: 36pt;"><strong><em><span style="color: #ff9900; text-decoration: underline;">Job Cost</span></em></strong></span></h1>
<div><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="/images/randomimages/features_image.jpg" alt="" /></div>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
</ul>
<ul>
<li>
<div>Unlimited tier-ing of levels for                                                   phasing/cost codes and billing                                                   codes and change orders, job cost to the line item.<img style="margin: 10px; float: right;" src="/images/stories/jobcosttab.jpg" alt="jobcosttab" width="522" height="458" /></div>
</li>
<li>
<div>Set up phases/cost codes and                                                   billing codes to match CSI                                                   libraries or your own.</div>
</li>
<li>
<div>Job Performance/Status area that                                                   allows tracking of job costs by take                                                   off line item. This area of the                                                    system facilitates a  multitude                                                  of ways to  implement job                                                    performance/status tracking.</div>
</li>
<li>
<div>Progress pay applications                                                   (percentage of completion or                                                    units). Handles sales tax on                                                  AIA equiv.·· Prints lien                                                  releases,  and change order                                                    requests. Progress pay                                                   applications can be customized                                                    by the user.</div>
</li>
<li>
<div>Print customizable progress or                                                   final lien releases for subs,                                                   suppliers, etc.</div>
</li>
<li>
<div>Change orders can be approved,                                                   unapproved,  pending-include or                                                   pending-exclude for both budgets                                                    and progress pay  applications.</div>
</li>
<li>
<div>Track change orders separately                                                  or under each phase/cost code.</div>
</li>
